cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with object recognition in unstructured environments using point cloud data. The use of neural networks for learning a robust latent representation of the 3D object suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper's focus on developing effective classification methods for autonomous vehicles, service robots, and surveillance drones suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. Finally, the use of feature descriptors and neural networks for object classification and retrieval suggests that it may also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
